      creating an application utilizing MVC architecture. It was a sprint to complete as much functionality as possible
      in
      the span of two weeks, with 3 other team members. A very enjoyable learning experience, it utilizes Express,
      Express-handlebars view engine, Sequelize ORM for modeling to a custom MySQL database, multer and aws-sdk for
      image
      uploads, and more.</p>
    <p> I was tasked with building
      most of the back end & database, and managing
      the git workflow from individual feature branches on up to the main branch and deployment via Heroku. As of this
